  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Camp Coordination and Camp Management and Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items (NFI) Assistance for Conflict Affected Populations in Northern Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The conflict in northern Ethiopia which began in November 2020 has spread from Tigray to Amhara and Afar regions resulting in the displacement of over two million people and the destruction of houses and household items. The displacement context in Ethiopia remains fluid as the country continues to experience conflict and natural disaster driven displacements. As the conflict spreads and deepens, it is expected to affect more people and cause further sporadic displacement and increase needs particularly in northern Ethiopia. As a result of increased displacement, the needs under the Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items (ES/NFI) and Camp Coordination and Camp management (CCCM) sectors in northern Ethiopia are immense. While most internally displaced persons (IDPs) (62% approx.) are seeking shelter with relatives and friends, many of the displaced (77% approx.) are living in crowded locations and sub-standard collective centres. Proposed interventions under this project address urgent gaps and needs identified through multi-sector assessments in Tigray and Amhara regions. IOM&#x2019;s response under this project includes CCCM interventions and provision of ES/NFIs.</narrative>
  </description>
